{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"57915d68-e445-42e3-a100-dedcfef19c08","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use the **lifecycle event mapping** in `MauiProgram.cs` via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android =>\n    {\n        android.OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is paused\n        });\n        android.OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is stopped\n        });\n    });\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios =>\n    {\n        ios.DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the app enters the background\n        });\n    });\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents` namespace.\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code separated.\n- Each platform exposes its native lifecycle events (e.g., `OnResume`, `WillTerminate`, etc.) through the same pattern.\n- This is configured in `CreateMauiApp()` alongside your other builder setup.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7c4a0a65-9ebf-4a7d-a50a-aa1142d05a3c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":386,"requestId":"044C:34A53A:B0A5ED:C97A5C:6A027A0C"},"id":"16fc005c-bb9e-4340-9f49-7127807d4ad6","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:53:40.074Z","parentId":"c188856f-9310-44e6-8b01-bdfdbd1a1f91"}
